decks.notes: The main objective of this deck is to control the game by countering opponent's spells, removing threats, and drawing cards efficiently. Cards like Force of Will, Counterspell, and Dovin's Veto help in countering important spells, while Supreme Verdict and Wrath of God deal with threats on the board. The deck also focuses on card advantage and selection with spells like Brainstorm, Preordain, and Mystic Confluence. The commander, Elminster, provides additional utility and card advantage with their abilities. This deck aims to stall the game, disrupt the opponent's strategy, and eventually win the game through incremental advantages and powerful late-game plays.

The main focus of this deck is to control the game by using a variety of counterspells, removal spells, and card draw. Atraxa, Grand Unifier serves as the commander and helps generate value over time with her proliferate ability. The deck includes powerful planeswalkers like Teferi, Hero of Dominaria and Teferi, Time Raveler to control the board and draw cards, as well as a wide range of versatile spells such as Cryptic Command and Supreme Verdict to deal with threats. The mana base is optimized with fetch lands and dual lands to ensure consistent mana production. Overall, the goal is to outvalue and outlast opponents through resource management and strategic decision-making.

The deck revolves around using Cloud, Midgar Mercenary as the commander to lead an aggressive, midrange strategy. The deck includes a variety of low-cost creatures and equipments to quickly establish a board presence and put pressure on the opponent. Cards like Puresteel Paladin and Stoneforge Mystic help to search for and equip powerful swords like Sword of Feast and Famine and Sword of Fire and Ice to deal additional damage and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck also features disruptive elements like Thalia, Guardian of Thraben and Drannith Magistrate to slow down the opponent while maintaining its aggressive tempo. With an emphasis on efficient creatures and equipment, the deck aims to close out the game quickly before the opponent can establish their own game plan.
